---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Kyrgyzstan Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/kyrgyzstan/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Kazakhstan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/kazakhstan' },
  { title: 'Uzbekistan for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/uzbekistan' },
  { title: 'Georgia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/georgia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'kyrgyzstanFit', header: 'Kyrgyzstan Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'KGS$38,250-54,640/mo', kyrgyzstanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'KGS$44,730-63,900/mo', kyrgyzstanFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'Allianz Care', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'KGS$34,425-49,175/mo', kyrgyzstanFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'Now Health', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: 'KGS$32,000-45,715/mo', kyrgyzstanFit: 'Very Good' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: 'KGS$34,425-54,640', annual: 'KGS$413K-655.7K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: 'KGS$47,220-72,850', annual: 'KGS$566.6K-874.2K' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: 'KGS$63,475-97,750', annual: 'KGS$761.7K-1.17M' },
  { category: 'Private Clinic (Bishkek)', monthly: 'KGS$2,000-5,000/visit', annual: 'Very affordable' },
  { category: 'Evacuation to Turkey', monthly: 'N/A', annual: 'KGS$2.5M-7.5M' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Kyrgyzstan 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors in Kyrgyzstan. Tian Shan mountains, Silk Road, very affordable living, and coverage for adventurous retirees 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Kyrgyzstan"
  subheadline="Kyrgyzstan offers stunning Tian Shan mountains, Issyk-Kul lake, nomadic yurt culture, Silk Road heritage, and extremely affordable living—Central Asia's adventure destination for budget-conscious mountain lovers."
  heroImage="/images/countries/kyrgyzstan-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Kyrgyzstan</h2>
  <p>
    Kyrgyzstan offers dramatic Tian Shan mountain scenery, beautiful Issyk-Kul lake, authentic nomadic yurt stays, Silk Road history, and extremely low cost of living. More democratic and open than Central Asian neighbors. For adventurous budget retirees seeking mountain beauty and cultural authenticity, Kyrgyzstan provides unique value.
  </p>

  <p>
    Bishkek is the capital with best healthcare—Soviet-era but improving. Issyk-Kul region offers lake resorts. Osh is southern cultural hub. Population ~7 million. Istanbul (5 hours) and Dubai (4 hours) provide medical backup. Almaty, Kazakhstan (4 hours drive) has better regional healthcare.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Limited; Turkey/Dubai evacuation common</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Kyrgyz, Russian widely spoken</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> KGS$50,000-100,000/month (~$580-1,160 USD); very affordable</li>
      <li><strong>Climate:</strong> Continental; cold winters; pleasant summers</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Mountains; nomadic; open society</li>
      <li><strong>Visa:</strong> Visa-free for many nationalities (60 days)</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Kyrgyzstan Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Kyrgyzstan healthcare is limited—National Hospital and some private clinics in Bishkek provide basic care. Soviet-era infrastructure. Limited specialists. Complex cases require evacuation to Istanbul (5-hour flight), Dubai (4 hours), or Almaty, Kazakhstan (4-hour drive with better hospitals).
  </p>

  <p>
    Private healthcare in Bishkek is affordable but basic. Mountains are remote with minimal healthcare access. International insurance with strong regional evacuation coverage essential.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Regional Evacuation Options</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Istanbul (5 hours) and Dubai (4 hours) provide world-class backup. Almaty, Kazakhstan is 4 hours by road with better regional care. Include Turkey/UAE and Kazakhstan in insurance coverage. Mountains are very remote—consider helicopter evacuation coverage for trekking.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Kyrgyzstan has very accessible visa policies:
  </p>

  <h3>Visa-Free Entry</h3>
  <p>
    60 days visa-free for many nationalities including US, EU, UK, Australia. Very welcoming policy.
  </p>

  <h3>Extended Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Extensions available. Simple process through OVIR (registration office).
  </p>

  <h3>Residence Permit</h3>
  <p>
    For longer stays. Various categories available. Apply through State Registration Service.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Nomad Friendly</h3>
  <p>
    Growing expat community. Bishkek has coworking spaces. Open, welcoming society.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Kyrgyzstan:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Entry:</strong> Travel insurance strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Extended stay:</strong> International coverage essential</li>
    <li><strong>Evacuation:</strong> Turkey/UAE coverage critical</li>
    <li><strong>Mountains:</strong> Consider high-altitude and helicopter coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Kyrgyzstan</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance with Turkey/Dubai evacuation essential. Consider Almaty coverage for regional care. High-altitude coverage important for mountain activities. Helicopter evacuation coverage recommended for remote trekking.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Kyrgyzstan, evacuation coverage critical:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Kyrgyzstan</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Strong regional network, Turkey access</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive</li>
    <li><strong>Istanbul access:</strong> Regional medical hub</li>
    <li><strong>Mountain coverage:</strong> High-altitude activities</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage for Kyrgyzstan with regional evacuation.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Kyrgyzstan (KGS ~86 to USD):
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Bishkek base:</strong> Best local healthcare</li>
    <li><strong>Extremely affordable:</strong> Very low living costs</li>
    <li><strong>Almaty option:</strong> Drive to Kazakhstan for routine care</li>
    <li><strong>Turkey network:</strong> Use for complex care</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: Mountain Trekker, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month pension. Bishkek base. Summer trekking.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Cigna Global with high-altitude coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~KGS$40,000/month (~$465). Adventure living; comprehensive backup.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Budget Retiree, 69</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,200/month budget. Issyk-Kul summers. Very frugal.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Allianz Care with essential coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~KGS$35,000/month (~$405). Maximum budget stretch; lake beauty.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: Silk Road Explorer, 67</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $2,000/month. Multi-country Central Asia rotation.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> BUPA Global with CIS coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> ~KGS$45,000/month (~$520). Regional exploration; comprehensive.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Kyrgyzstan safe?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Generally safe—most democratic Central Asian country. Some political instability (revolutions in 2005, 2010, 2020) but tourists rarely affected. Southern border areas with Tajikistan occasionally tense. Bishkek and tourist areas safe. Normal precautions apply.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Do I need Russian?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Very helpful—Russian widely spoken, more so than Kyrgyz in cities. English very limited outside tourism. Healthcare in Russian. Learning Russian basics opens many doors. Young people may know some English.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What about altitude?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Significant consideration—Bishkek is 800m but mountains reach 7,000m+. Issyk-Kul is 1,600m. Popular treks involve 3,000-4,000m passes. Altitude sickness real risk. Acclimatization essential. May not be suitable for those with heart/lung conditions.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Why Kyrgyzstan over Kazakhstan?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        More dramatic mountains, more affordable, more open society. Kazakhstan has better healthcare and infrastructure. Kyrgyzstan has better scenery and authenticity. Kazakhstan for practicality; Kyrgyzstan for adventure.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers for Kyrgyzstan coverage.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/allianz-care" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Allianz Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Healthcare in Kyrgyzstan is limited—evacuation coverage essential. Altitude considerations important. Always verify current requirements.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
